00:00:16.680 --> 00:00:20.100 align:middle line:10%
During the 1950s and '60s,
there was a worldwide movement

00:00:20.100 --> 00:00:22.740 align:middle line:10%
of people in countries
that had recently

00:00:22.740 --> 00:00:25.810 align:middle line:10%
been colonies of Europe
throughout Africa, Asia,

00:00:25.810 --> 00:00:28.830 align:middle line:10%
and much of the Middle East,
as well as other small nations

00:00:28.830 --> 00:00:31.290 align:middle line:10%
in the Western hemisphere
that for all intents

00:00:31.290 --> 00:00:33.870 align:middle line:10%
and purposes were colonies
of the United States.

00:00:33.870 --> 00:00:37.860 align:middle line:84%
In all these places, people
had the same basic issue--

00:00:37.860 --> 00:00:40.410 align:middle line:84%
inequality, poverty,
and the need

00:00:40.410 --> 00:00:43.560 align:middle line:84%
for serious social
reforms, land reform

00:00:43.560 --> 00:00:46.080 align:middle line:90%
probably being at the top.

00:00:46.080 --> 00:00:48.840 align:middle line:84%
If America were an openly
expansionist nation

00:00:48.840 --> 00:00:51.810 align:middle line:84%
like Germany or Japan
of the Second World War,

00:00:51.810 --> 00:00:54.810 align:middle line:84%
the charade might not have
needed to be so elaborate.

00:00:54.810 --> 00:00:58.890 align:middle line:84%
Sure, Germany and Japan both
did international false flags,

00:00:58.890 --> 00:01:01.620 align:middle line:84%
but those were incredibly
crude compared with the levels

00:01:01.620 --> 00:01:03.750 align:middle line:90%
achieved by the United States.

00:01:03.750 --> 00:01:07.740 align:middle line:84%
Simply put, America's rhetoric
and posturing about freedom

00:01:07.740 --> 00:01:11.190 align:middle line:84%
forced Americans to
become far, far better

00:01:11.190 --> 00:01:13.070 align:middle line:90%
at the art of the false flag.

00:01:13.070 --> 00:01:15.180 align:middle line:84%
A perfect example of this
is what is known today

00:01:15.180 --> 00:01:17.250 align:middle line:90%
as the color revolution.

00:01:17.250 --> 00:01:18.990 align:middle line:84%
After the end of
the Cold War, there

00:01:18.990 --> 00:01:20.760 align:middle line:84%
were a series of
what appeared to be

00:01:20.760 --> 00:01:24.410 align:middle line:84%
mostly peaceful democratic
uprisings in Eastern Europe,

00:01:24.410 --> 00:01:27.390 align:middle line:84%
in what was formerly
part of the Soviet Union.

00:01:27.390 --> 00:01:29.940 align:middle line:84%
In 2003, the nation
of Georgia had what

00:01:29.940 --> 00:01:32.220 align:middle line:90%
was called the Rose Revolution.

00:01:32.220 --> 00:01:36.390 align:middle line:84%
In 2004, Ukraine had the
Orange Revolution, and so on.

00:01:36.390 --> 00:01:39.270 align:middle line:84%
These became called
color revolutions.

00:01:39.270 --> 00:01:42.390 align:middle line:84%
Was it coincidence that
all of these revolutions

00:01:42.390 --> 00:01:43.830 align:middle line:84%
ended up with the
new governments

00:01:43.830 --> 00:01:46.600 align:middle line:84%
being closer to the United
States, Europe and the IMF

00:01:46.600 --> 00:01:49.110 align:middle line:90%
and less friendly toward Russia?

00:01:49.110 --> 00:01:52.560 align:middle line:84%
But in fact, the United States
had mastered this art form

00:01:52.560 --> 00:01:57.000 align:middle line:84%
back in the 1950s, long before
anyone came up with the term.

00:01:57.000 --> 00:01:59.190 align:middle line:84%
This form of regime
change, one that

00:01:59.190 --> 00:02:01.920 align:middle line:84%
wears the trappings
of popular revolt,

00:02:01.920 --> 00:02:04.410 align:middle line:84%
often works better
than military coups

00:02:04.410 --> 00:02:08.310 align:middle line:84%
because they seem like genuine
expressions of the people.

00:02:08.310 --> 00:02:10.289 align:middle line:84%
It's fair to call
color revolution

00:02:10.289 --> 00:02:12.390 align:middle line:84%
a form of false
flag, and we really

00:02:12.390 --> 00:02:14.610 align:middle line:84%
ought to take a
closer look at them.

00:02:14.610 --> 00:02:16.290 align:middle line:84%
There are certain
fundamentals of how

00:02:16.290 --> 00:02:19.170 align:middle line:84%
to create your own
revolution in another country

00:02:19.170 --> 00:02:21.330 align:middle line:84%
or in your own country,
for that matter.

00:02:21.330 --> 00:02:24.540 align:middle line:84%
Step one-- start
with lots of money.

00:02:24.540 --> 00:02:26.880 align:middle line:84%
It all goes toward
funding your core leaders

00:02:26.880 --> 00:02:28.620 align:middle line:90%
to build the organization.

00:02:28.620 --> 00:02:31.950 align:middle line:84%
We're talking many millions
of dollars, and maybe billions

00:02:31.950 --> 00:02:34.860 align:middle line:84%
if the need is strong enough
and the target is worth it.

00:02:34.860 --> 00:02:37.500 align:middle line:84%
Step two-- your
core leaders hire

00:02:37.500 --> 00:02:40.020 align:middle line:84%
the key workers and
trainers, the foot soldiers

00:02:40.020 --> 00:02:41.160 align:middle line:90%
of the movement.

00:02:41.160 --> 00:02:45.390 align:middle line:84%
Step three-- create social
media and news infrastructure.

00:02:45.390 --> 00:02:48.690 align:middle line:84%
Any modern movement has to have
sophisticated social media.

00:02:48.690 --> 00:02:51.480 align:middle line:84%
We're talking Facebook pages,
Twitter feeds, Instagram,

00:02:51.480 --> 00:02:53.160 align:middle line:90%
and of course, a good website.

00:02:53.160 --> 00:02:56.370 align:middle line:84%
Step four-- create
physical infrastructure.

00:02:56.370 --> 00:02:58.350 align:middle line:84%
We're talking
office space, tents

00:02:58.350 --> 00:03:00.610 align:middle line:84%
if you want shantytowns
or long-term protest

00:03:00.610 --> 00:03:03.080 align:middle line:84%
sites, wooden platforms
and structures

00:03:03.080 --> 00:03:07.230 align:middle line:84%
for speeches, signs, banners,
lots and lots of signage.

00:03:07.230 --> 00:03:12.060 align:middle line:84%
Step five-- create an event, the
event that sparks the movement.

00:03:12.060 --> 00:03:14.520 align:middle line:84%
Only when the
infrastructure is ready

00:03:14.520 --> 00:03:17.050 align:middle line:90%
do you then need the event.

00:03:17.050 --> 00:03:19.830 align:middle line:84%
This is the rallying point
around which your movement

00:03:19.830 --> 00:03:21.750 align:middle line:90%
can generate interest.

00:03:21.750 --> 00:03:24.510 align:middle line:84%
It could be an election that
you choose to contest or someone

00:03:24.510 --> 00:03:26.370 align:middle line:84%
in prison that you
can politicize.

00:03:26.370 --> 00:03:28.320 align:middle line:84%
It could be corruption
of the government.

00:03:28.320 --> 00:03:31.680 align:middle line:84%
It could be ethnic or
class or racial oppression.

00:03:31.680 --> 00:03:35.400 align:middle line:84%
Whatever it is, it has to make
sense within your society.

00:03:35.400 --> 00:03:38.040 align:middle line:90%
Step six-- include the public.

00:03:38.040 --> 00:03:39.570 align:middle line:84%
Once you have
created your event,

00:03:39.570 --> 00:03:43.080 align:middle line:84%
now you use your foot soldiers
and get the public involved.

00:03:43.080 --> 00:03:46.470 align:middle line:84%
Once they see that there's
an actual political movement

00:03:46.470 --> 00:03:48.900 align:middle line:84%
and that it appears to
be a natural response

00:03:48.900 --> 00:03:51.000 align:middle line:84%
to some injustice,
you'll probably

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:53.340 align:middle line:84%
get some public attendance
at your rallies.

00:03:53.340 --> 00:03:55.080 align:middle line:84%
This is the
make-or-break moment,

00:03:55.080 --> 00:03:58.870 align:middle line:84%
since the movement has to appear
to have broad public support,

00:03:58.870 --> 00:04:00.510 align:middle line:90%
or it won't succeed.

00:04:00.510 --> 00:04:03.840 align:middle line:84%
Step seven-- provoke
a police response.

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:06.540 align:middle line:84%
This is dangerous, but
obviously can be effective.

00:04:06.540 --> 00:04:08.880 align:middle line:84%
It will help to polarize
your society, which

00:04:08.880 --> 00:04:10.680 align:middle line:90%
ultimately helps your cause.

00:04:10.680 --> 00:04:14.790 align:middle line:84%
Provoking police response
will require very selective

00:04:14.790 --> 00:04:16.649 align:middle line:90%
video recording and editing.

00:04:16.649 --> 00:04:18.600 align:middle line:84%
Then you display
it on social media.

00:04:18.600 --> 00:04:21.390 align:middle line:84%
This means demonstrating
police violence in some form,

00:04:21.390 --> 00:04:22.800 align:middle line:90%
but it's all in the editing.

00:04:22.800 --> 00:04:24.330 align:middle line:84%
Post your clip to
prove to the world

00:04:24.330 --> 00:04:26.520 align:middle line:84%
how repressive
the government is.

00:04:26.520 --> 00:04:28.950 align:middle line:84%
Step eight-- once
you have what appears

00:04:28.950 --> 00:04:32.040 align:middle line:84%
to be a genuine movement,
you can now enlist support

00:04:32.040 --> 00:04:33.930 align:middle line:90%
from local politicians.

00:04:33.930 --> 00:04:35.940 align:middle line:84%
Once that happens,
you have sanction,

00:04:35.940 --> 00:04:39.090 align:middle line:84%
as it were, from at least
some of the official power

00:04:39.090 --> 00:04:40.230 align:middle line:90%
structure.

00:04:40.230 --> 00:04:43.200 align:middle line:84%
Step nine-- get the
attention of Western media.

00:04:43.200 --> 00:04:44.940 align:middle line:84%
If the funding
behind this movement

00:04:44.940 --> 00:04:48.660 align:middle line:84%
is the CIA or powerful groups
with the right connections,

00:04:48.660 --> 00:04:50.490 align:middle line:84%
then this step has
already been prepared,

00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:53.010 align:middle line:84%
but now is the time
for coverage to begin.

00:04:53.010 --> 00:04:55.150 align:middle line:90%
And that leads to step 10--

00:04:55.150 --> 00:04:57.390 align:middle line:90%
enlisting international support.

00:04:57.390 --> 00:05:00.420 align:middle line:84%
When the US officially
condemns the repressive actions

00:05:00.420 --> 00:05:02.550 align:middle line:84%
of the government in
question and supports

00:05:02.550 --> 00:05:05.910 align:middle line:84%
your popular uprising, you
