00:05:22.150 --> 00:05:25.330 align:middle line:84%
We'll start with the
nation of Iran in 1953.

00:05:25.330 --> 00:05:27.730 align:middle line:84%
To this day, America's
operation there

00:05:27.730 --> 00:05:32.600 align:middle line:84%
is a classic example of false
flag and regime change success.

00:05:32.600 --> 00:05:34.690 align:middle line:84%
And by the way, let's not
leave out the British,

00:05:34.690 --> 00:05:37.550 align:middle line:84%
because this was definitely
a joint operation.

00:05:37.550 --> 00:05:40.300 align:middle line:84%
Let's take a look
at Operation Ajax.

00:05:40.300 --> 00:05:42.300 align:middle line:10%
Throughout the first
half of the 20th century,

00:05:42.300 --> 00:05:46.660 align:middle line:10%
Iran with its massive oil fields
was under British domination,

00:05:46.660 --> 00:05:48.880 align:middle line:10%
its oil under the
profitable control

00:05:48.880 --> 00:05:51.010 align:middle line:10%
of a British
corporation known rather

00:05:51.010 --> 00:05:54.610 align:middle line:10%
dishonestly as the
Anglo-Iranian Oil Company.

00:05:54.610 --> 00:05:56.530 align:middle line:10%
But make no mistake,
this operation

00:05:56.530 --> 00:05:58.390 align:middle line:10%
was British all the
way and had been

00:05:58.390 --> 00:06:02.950 align:middle line:10%
controlling the Iranian
oil industry since 1913.

00:06:02.950 --> 00:06:06.570 align:middle line:84%
Today, by the way, that company
is known as British Petroleum.

00:06:06.570 --> 00:06:10.060 align:middle line:84%
In 1951, a politician
named Mohammad Mosaddegh

00:06:10.060 --> 00:06:12.490 align:middle line:90%
became Prime Minister of Iran.

00:06:12.490 --> 00:06:15.910 align:middle line:84%
Mosaddegh was a remarkable
man and a true progressive.

00:06:15.910 --> 00:06:18.220 align:middle line:84%
Immediately, his government
introduced reforms

00:06:18.220 --> 00:06:22.360 align:middle line:84%
like social security and
much needed land reforms.

00:06:22.360 --> 00:06:25.050 align:middle line:84%
All these made him very
popular with the people.

00:06:25.050 --> 00:06:27.200 align:middle line:90%
But then he did the unthinkable.

00:06:27.200 --> 00:06:29.680 align:middle line:90%
He challenged the oil industry.

00:06:29.680 --> 00:06:33.190 align:middle line:84%
Initially, he tried to audit
the Anglo-Iranian Oil Company

00:06:33.190 --> 00:06:36.670 align:middle line:84%
and earn a 50/50 cut from
the company's profits.

00:06:36.670 --> 00:06:40.000 align:middle line:84%
When he received no cooperation,
the Iranian parliament

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.110 align:middle line:84%
voted to nationalize
Iran's oil industry.

00:06:44.110 --> 00:06:45.730 align:middle line:84%
REPORTER: Mosaddegh
wanted none of it.

00:06:45.730 --> 00:06:49.400 align:middle line:90%
