Iranian government.

00:10:11.710 --> 00:10:14.110 align:middle line:84%
And of course, no one
gave the slightest hint

00:10:14.110 --> 00:10:16.370 align:middle line:84%
that this was a
covert operation.

00:10:16.370 --> 00:10:17.590 align:middle line:90%
Why would they?

00:10:17.590 --> 00:10:21.050 align:middle line:84%
Were deeply in bed with
both CIA and MI6 themselves,

00:10:21.050 --> 00:10:23.890 align:middle line:84%
except that ordinary
people had no idea.

00:10:23.890 --> 00:10:26.920 align:middle line:84%
The Ajax operation
was wildly successful.

00:10:26.920 --> 00:10:30.640 align:middle line:10%
It deposed a popular government
working on behalf of the people

00:10:30.640 --> 00:10:32.650 align:middle line:10%
to salvage the oil
companies that were

00:10:32.650 --> 00:10:34.690 align:middle line:10%
the real owners of the country.

00:10:34.690 --> 00:10:37.360 align:middle line:84%
A big part of the price
the US got out of it

00:10:37.360 --> 00:10:40.630 align:middle line:84%
was a major piece of
the Iranian oil action.

00:10:40.630 --> 00:10:43.390 align:middle line:84%
So the Brits no
longer had a monopoly.

00:10:43.390 --> 00:10:45.730 align:middle line:10%
And the Iranian
people, well, they

00:10:45.730 --> 00:10:49.180 align:middle line:10%
got 26 years of the Shah,
who remained a loyal client

00:10:49.180 --> 00:10:52.360 align:middle line:10%
of the United States and of
David Rockefeller for the rest

00:10:52.360 --> 00:10:56.080 align:middle line:10%
of his days, becoming especially
known for his opulent lifestyle

00:10:56.080 --> 00:10:58.560 align:middle line:10%
and repressive political police.

00:10:58.560 --> 00:11:00.610 align:middle line:84%
The operation taught
the United States

00:11:00.610 --> 00:11:03.520 align:middle line:84%
that it could fake a popular
uprising as long as they

00:11:03.520 --> 00:11:06.220 align:middle line:84%
threw enough money around,
hired enough thugs to break

00:11:06.220 --> 00:11:08.350 align:middle line:84%
things and kill people,
and had a compliant

00:11:08.350 --> 00:11:10.255 align:middle line:90%
media to watch its back.

00:11:10.255 --> 00:11:14.930 align:middle line:84%
The US outdid itself the
following year in 1954.

00:11:14.930 --> 00:11:16.690 align:middle line:84%
This was a false
flag regime change

00:11:16.690 --> 00:11:19.750 align:middle line:84%
operation against the
nation of Guatemala.

00:11:19.750 --> 00:11:22.120 align:middle line:84%
Guatemala, one of the
poorest nations in the world,

00:11:22.120 --> 00:11:25.360 align:middle line:84%
had been controlled by
US corporations in power

00:11:25.360 --> 00:11:27.280 align:middle line:90%
seemingly forever.

00:11:27.280 --> 00:11:30.130 align:middle line:84%
The best land was owned by the
American corporation United

00:11:30.130 --> 00:11:31.060 align:middle line:90%
Fruit.

00:11:31.060 --> 00:11:32.740 align:middle line:90%
The people lived in poverty.

00:11:32.740 --> 00:11:35.230 align:middle line:84%
In 1944, there was
a popular revolution

00:11:35.230 --> 00:11:37.900 align:middle line:84%
against the dictator,
which led to Guatemala's

00:11:37.900 --> 00:11:41.110 align:middle line:84%
first democratic election
and major social reforms

00:11:41.110 --> 00:11:45.070 align:middle line:84%
like minimum wage, better
education, improved labor laws,

00:11:45.070 --> 00:11:47.170 align:middle line:90%
and expanded voting rights.

00:11:47.170 --> 00:11:50.770 align:middle line:84%
In 1950, President
Jacobo Arbenz began

00:11:50.770 --> 00:11:53.290 align:middle line:84%
pressing for land
reform, probably

00:11:53.290 --> 00:11:56.980 align:middle line:84%
the most important issue
in Guatemala at that time.

00:11:56.980 --> 00:11:58.930 align:middle line:84%
The main idea was
to give poor farmers

00:11:58.930 --> 00:12:03.860 align:middle line:84%
access to the vast, unused
lands owned by United Fruit.

00:12:03.860 --> 00:12:07.910 align:middle line:84%
You can imagine how popular
this would be in such a country.

00:12:07.910 --> 00:12:09.980 align:middle line:84%
In America, President
Harry Truman

00:12:09.980 --> 00:12:13.170 align:middle line:84%
authorized a coup
against Arbenz in 1952,

00:12:13.170 --> 00:12:16.130 align:middle line:84%
but it was aborted when
details leaked out.

00:12:16.130 --> 00:12:19.940 align:middle line:10%
Then in 1953, Dwight
Eisenhower became President,

00:12:19.940 --> 00:12:22.820 align:middle line:10%
bringing into his cabinet
the Dulles brothers, John

00:12:22.820 --> 00:12:23.920 align:middle line:10%
and Allen.

00:12:23.920 --> 00:12:26.660 align:middle line:84%
One ran the State
Department, one ran CIA,

00:12:26.660 --> 00:12:29.600 align:middle line:84%
and both were heavily
connected to United Fruit.

00:12:29.600 --> 00:12:32.390 align:middle line:84%
Eisenhower authorized the
CIA to carry out a coup

00:12:32.390 --> 00:12:35.390 align:middle line:90%
operation against Guatemala.

00:12:35.390 --> 00:12:37.340 align:middle line:84%
The CIA decided
they needed to show

00:12:37.340 --> 00:12:39.770 align:middle line:84%
that Arbenz's
government was communist

00:12:39.770 --> 00:12:42.200 align:middle line:90%
and under Soviet control.

00:12:42.200 --> 00:12:45.680 align:middle line:84%
First, in February
1954, the CIA planted

00:12:45.680 --> 00:12:48.290 align:middle line:84%
weapons in next-door
Nicaragua that

00:12:48.290 --> 00:12:50.300 align:middle line:84%
was supposed to
link to the Soviets

00:12:50.300 --> 00:12:53.240 align:middle line:84%
and prove that Guatemala was
under control from Moscow.

00:12:53.240 --> 00:12:56.660 align:middle line:10%
The president of Nicaragua,
Anastasio Somoza Garcia,

00:12:56.660 --> 00:12:59.060 align:middle line:10%
was in on the fix,
and told the press

00:12:59.060 --> 00:13:01.520 align:middle line:10%
that a Soviet submarine
had been photographed,

00:13:01.520 --> 00:13:04.010 align:middle line:10%
although no images
were available.

00:13:04.010 --> 00:13:07.970 align:middle line:84%
Somoza also floated a story
about Guatemalan assassination

00:13:07.970 --> 00:13:11.310 align:middle line:84%
squads that no one
seemed to believe.

00:13:11.310 --> 00:13:15.000 align:middle line:84%
The CIA also gathered a large
amount of Soviet-marked weapons

00:13:15.000 --> 00:13:18.510 align:middle line:84%
to plant them inside
Guatemala before the invasion.

00:13:18.510 --> 00:13:22.170 align:middle line:84%
The whole point, of course, was
to prove Russian intervention.

00:13:22.170 --> 00:13:24.270 align:middle line:84%
The CIA also bribed
certain members

00:13:24.270 --> 00:13:28.300 align:middle line:84%
of the Guatemalan officer corps
to get them to join the rebels.

00:13:28.300 --> 00:13:30.930 align:middle line:84%
They set up radio
stations inside Guatemala

00:13:30.930 --> 00:13:34.680 align:middle line:84%
and posed as rebels trying to
get recruits for the movement.

00:13:34.680 --> 00:13:36.750 align:middle line:10%
One lie that they
told on the radio

00:13:36.750 --> 00:13:40.380 align:middle line:10%
was that Arbenz was secretly
planning to disband or disarm

00:13:40.380 --> 00:13:44.250 align:middle line:10%
the armed forces and replace
it with a people's militia.

00:13:44.250 --> 00:13:47.310 align:middle line:10%
CIA planes dropped
leaflets over Guatemala

00:13:47.310 --> 00:13:49.200 align:middle line:10%
carrying the same message.

00:13:49.200 --> 00:13:51.360 align:middle line:84%
The CIA even offered
Arbenz himself

00:13:51.360 --> 00:13:54.060 align:middle line:84%
a bribe, possibly to
abdicate or something less.

00:13:54.060 --> 00:13:55.209 align:middle line:90%
We're not sure.

00:13:55.209 --> 00:13:57.750 align:middle line:84%
They dumped a lot of money for
him into a Swiss bank account,

00:13:57.750 --> 00:13:59.040 align:middle line:90%
but he rejected it.

00:13:59.040 --> 00:14:02.250 align:middle line:84%
An office called the US
Information Agency, essentially

00:14:02.250 --> 00:14:05.970 align:middle line:84%
a CIA outfit, started
placing unattributed articles

00:14:05.970 --> 00:14:09.450 align:middle line:84%
in foreign newspapers labeling
certain Guatemalan officials

00:14:09.450 --> 00:14:10.584 align:middle line:90%
as communists.

00:14:10.584 --> 00:14:12.000 align:middle line:84%
They referred to
different actions

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:15.500 align:middle line:84%
by the Guatemalan government
as communist-inspired.

00:14:15.500 --> 00:14:19.140 align:middle line:84%
In just a few weeks before
the coup of June 1954,

00:14:19.140 --> 00:14:22.470 align:middle line:84%
more than 200 articles
about Guatemala

00:14:22.470 --> 00:14:26.040 align:middle line:84%
were written and published
across Latin America.

00:14:26.040 --> 00:14:28.230 align:middle line:84%
This became a standard
American practice--

00:14:28.230 --> 00:14:32.010 align:middle line:84%
publish a story abroad and watch
it spread around the world.

00:14:32.010 --> 00:14:35.310 align:middle line:84%
All this gave the appearance
that independent world opinion

00:14:35.310 --> 00:14:38.200 align:middle line:84%
was taking a certain stand, and
it kept America's connection

00:14:38.200 --> 00:14:39.000 align:middle line:90%
hidden.

00:14:39.000 --> 00:14:41.457 align:middle line:10%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:14:41.457 --> 00:14:44.040 align:middle line:10%
>> JOHN CANNON: US Secretary of
State Dulles takes the rostrum

00:14:44.040 --> 00:14:46.790 align:middle line:10%
to urge united action by
the Americas to outlaw

00:14:46.790 --> 00:14:49.100 align:middle line:10%
international communist
intervention in the Western

00:14:49.100 --> 00:14:50.300 align:middle line:10%
hemisphere.

00:14:50.300 --> 00:14:53.180 align:middle line:10%
>> JOHN DULLES: This conference
was shocked by the dastardly

00:14:53.180 --> 00:14:57.290 align:middle line:10%
attack on members of the United
States Congress by those who

00:14:57.290 --> 00:15:01.230 align:middle line:10%
professed to be patriots.

00:15:01.230 --> 00:15:04.220 align:middle line:84%
They may not themselves
have been communists,

00:15:04.220 --> 00:15:07.570 align:middle line:84%
but they had been subjected
to the inflammatory influence

00:15:07.570 --> 00:15:12.860 align:middle line:84%
of communism, which avowedly
uses extreme nationalism as one

00:15:12.860 --> 00:15:14.420 align:middle line:90%
of its tools.

00:15:14.420 --> 00:15:15.980 align:middle line:84%
>> RICHARD: Shortly
before the coup,

00:15:15.980 --> 00:15:19.100 align:middle line:84%
Nicaraguan president Somoza
got back into the picture

00:15:19.100 --> 00:15:22.760 align:middle line:84%
and announced that his police
had discovered a secret Soviet

00:15:22.760 --> 00:15:24.230 align:middle line:90%
shipment of weapons.

00:15:24.230 --> 00:15:27.080 align:middle line:84%
Of course, these had
been planted by the CIA.

00:15:27.080 --> 00:15:29.000 align:middle line:84%
And finally, just
before the invasion,

00:15:29.000 --> 00:15:32.930 align:middle line:84%
an unmarked plane parachuted
weapons with Soviet markings

00:15:32.930 --> 00:15:34.700 align:middle line:90%
into Guatemala.

00:15:34.700 --> 00:15:37.070 align:middle line:84%
>> REPORTER: Guatemala City,
representatives of the new

00:15:37.070 --> 00:15:39.890 align:middle line:84%
anti-communist government,
inspect $10 million worth

00:15:39.890 --> 00:15:42.500 align:middle line:84%
of arms that were sold to
the deposed red government

00:15:42.500 --> 00:15:44.390 align:middle line:90%
of President Arbenz.

00:15:44.390 --> 00:15:47.570 align:middle line:84%
Manufactured in Czechoslovakia,
and delivered by Polish ships,

00:15:47.570 --> 00:15:49.050 align:middle line:84%
the collection was
supposed to help

00:15:49.050 --> 00:15:51.260 align:middle line:84%
the commies to
suppress the rebellion

00:15:51.260 --> 00:15:52.589 align:middle line:90%
against their tyranny.

00:15:52.589 --> 00:15:55.130 align:middle line:84%
>> RICHARD: When, by the way,
some of the CIA's operation was

00:15:55.130 --> 00:15:59.750 align:middle line:84%
exposed in late January 1954,
the State Department simply

00:15:59.750 --> 00:16:03.170 align:middle line:84%
called the accusations
ridiculous and untrue.

00:16:03.170 --> 00:16:05.540 align:middle line:84%
The US press was
completely on board.

00:16:05.540 --> 00:16:08.540 align:middle line:10%
Time Magazine ridiculed
the idea that Americans

00:16:08.540 --> 00:16:11.540 align:middle line:10%
would engage in a coup and said
the accusations were, quote,

00:16:11.540 --> 00:16:14.270 align:middle line:10%
"masterminded in Moscow."

00:16:14.270 --> 00:16:16.520 align:middle line:10%
The coup itself was
almost a denouement.

00:16:16.520 --> 00:16:18.230 align:middle line:10%
The CIA armed and
trained a force

00:16:18.230 --> 00:16:20.930 align:middle line:10%
of 480 men, not large at all.

00:16:20.930 --> 00:16:23.510 align:middle line:84%
They invaded Guatemala from
bases in Honduras and El

00:16:23.510 --> 00:16:27.120 align:middle line:90%
Salvador on June 18, 1954.

00:16:27.120 --> 00:16:29.480 align:middle line:84%
But it was the
psychological warfare

00:16:29.480 --> 00:16:33.140 align:middle line:84%
that did the trick, including
setting up an anti-Arbenz radio

00:16:33.140 --> 00:16:36.650 align:middle line:84%
station claiming to be
giving genuine news.

00:16:36.650 --> 00:16:38.900 align:middle line:84%
Some of the CIA broadcasts
were transmitted

00:16:38.900 --> 00:16:42.410 align:middle line:84%
over regular public radio, and
some over military channels,

00:16:42.410 --> 00:16:44.120 align:middle line:90%
all very convincing.

00:16:44.120 --> 00:16:48.440 align:middle line:84%
During one nighttime raid, a
tape recording of a bomb attack

00:16:48.440 --> 00:16:50.900 align:middle line:84%
was actually played
over loudspeakers

00:16:50.900 --> 00:16:53.060 align:middle line:84%
set up on the roof
of the US embassy

00:16:53.060 --> 00:16:54.410 align:middle line:90%
just to scare the people.

00:16:54.410 --> 00:16:57.530 align:middle line:84%
When Arbenz went on the air
to try and calm everyone down,

00:16:57.530 --> 00:17:00.260 align:middle line:90%
the CIA jammed his broadcast.

00:17:00.260 --> 00:17:02.028 align:middle line:84%
There were also
dummy parachute drops

00:17:02.028 --> 00:17:04.069 align:middle line:84%
to make people think it
was a major invasion that

00:17:04.069 --> 00:17:05.829 align:middle line:90%
was going on.

00:17:05.829 --> 00:17:08.240 align:middle line:84%
United Fruit circulated
photographs of what they said

00:17:08.240 --> 00:17:10.460 align:middle line:84%
were mutilated bodies
about to be buried

00:17:10.460 --> 00:17:13.940 align:middle line:84%
in a mass grave, examples,
they said, of the atrocities

00:17:13.940 --> 00:17:16.640 align:middle line:90%
committed by the Arbenz regime.

00:17:16.640 --> 00:17:20.270 align:middle line:84%
The Guatemalan military realized
that this was a US operation,

00:17:20.270 --> 00:17:22.310 align:middle line:84%
and for that reason,
it seems, refused

00:17:22.310 --> 00:17:26.000 align:middle line:84%
to fight out of terror that
the US would actually invade.

00:17:26.000 --> 00:17:28.460 align:middle line:84%
Arbenz resigned a week
later, and the CIA

00:17:28.460 --> 00:17:29.960 align:middle line:90%
set up the new government.

00:17:29.960 --> 00:17:33.245 align:middle line:84%
>> MAN: This is the first time
in the history of the world

00:17:33.245 --> 00:17:35.785 align:middle line:84%
that the communist government
has been overthrown

00:17:35.785 --> 00:17:37.060 align:middle line:90%
by the people.

00:17:37.060 --> 00:17:39.080 align:middle line:84%
And for that, we
congratulate you

00:17:39.080 --> 00:17:42.720 align:middle line:84%
and the people of Guatemala for
the support they have given.

00:17:42.720 --> 00:17:45.770 align:middle line:84%
>> RICHARD: The US media was
utterly servile in reporting

00:17:45.770 --> 00:17:49.040 align:middle line:84%
things just as the US
government wanted them to.

00:17:49.040 --> 00:17:52.010 align:middle line:84%
And meanwhile, the United States
truly dealt the death blow

00:17:52.010 --> 00:17:53.645 align:middle line:90%
to Guatemalan democracy.

00:17:53.645 --> 00:17:55.520 align:middle line:84%
Through the rest of the
century, that country

00:17:55.520 --> 00:17:59.090 align:middle line:84%
was beset by dictatorship,
civil war, and human rights

00:17:59.090 --> 00:18:00.170 align:middle line:90%
violations.

00:18:00.170 --> 00:18:02.657 align:middle line:84%
But American
corporations were happy.

00:18:02.657 --> 00:18:04.990 align:middle line:84%
>> REPORTER: Well, the facts
show that the rebellion now

00:18:04.990 --> 00:18:08.720 align:middle line:84%
disturbing Central America
is one conducted by patriotic

00:18:08.720 --> 00:18:12.560 align:middle line:84%
anti-red Guatemalans, which
inspires Russia to air

00:18:12.560 --> 00:18:16.340 align:middle line:84%
the worn-out charge that
the US created the trouble.

00:18:16.340 --> 00:18:18.890 align:middle line:84%
>> RICHARD: The operations in
Iran and Guatemala emboldened

00:18:18.890 --> 00:18:23.030 align:middle line:84%
America's CIA into thinking it
had carte blanche with the less

00:18:23.030 --> 00:18:25.130 align:middle line:90%
powerful nations in the world.

00:18:25.130 --> 00:18:27.380 align:middle line:84%
Regime change became
a point of pride

00:18:27.380 --> 00:18:30.950 align:middle line:84%
within people in the CIA's
clandestine operations.

00:18:30.950 --> 00:18:32.515 align:middle line:90%
And then came Cuba.

00:18:32.515 --> 00:18:36.446 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:18:36.446 --> 00:18:38.820 align:middle line:84%
>> REPORTER: From his stronghold
in the wild Sierra Madre

00:18:38.820 --> 00:18:42.270 align:middle line:84%
Mountains, Cuba's Fidel Castro
emerged triumphant after two

00:18:42.270 --> 00:18:45.540 align:middle line:84%
years of guerrilla warfare
against the Batista regime.

00:18:45.540 --> 00:18:48.240 align:middle line:84%
>> RICHARD: Cuba had always
been a loyal economic appendage

00:18:48.240 --> 00:18:52.020 align:middle line:84%
of the United States, as well as
home to organized crime money,

00:18:52.020 --> 00:18:54.990 align:middle line:84%
some of which happened
to be close to the CIA.

00:18:54.990 --> 00:18:58.530 align:middle line:10%
At the beginning of 1959,
a revolutionary movement

00:18:58.530 --> 00:19:03.420 align:middle line:10%
led by Fidel Castro did the
unthinkable and took power.

00:19:03.420 --> 00:19:06.130 align:middle line:84%
In March 1960,
President Eisenhower

00:19:06.130 --> 00:19:11.850 align:middle line:84%
allocated $13 million for the
CIA to plan Castro's overthrow.

00:19:11.850 --> 00:19:15.420 align:middle line:10%
A few months later in
early January 1961,

00:19:15.420 --> 00:19:18.540 align:middle line:10%
not long before he left the
White House to John F. Kennedy,

00:19:18.540 --> 00:19:20.520 align:middle line:10%
Eisenhower told the
head of the Joint Chiefs

00:19:20.520 --> 00:19:24.810 align:middle line:10%
of Staff, Lyman Lemnitzer, that
he would move against Castro

00:19:24.810 --> 00:19:28.500 align:middle line:10%
before the inauguration if
only the Cubans gave him

00:19:28.500 --> 00:19:30.510 align:middle line:10%
a really good excuse.

00:19:30.510 --> 00:19:32.940 align:middle line:90%
Then, Ike put out an idea.

00:19:32.940 --> 00:19:36.550 align:middle line:84%
If Castro didn't give a
good excuse, maybe they--

00:19:36.550 --> 00:19:38.070 align:middle line:90%
and this is a quote--

00:19:38.070 --> 00:19:40.800 align:middle line:84%
"could think of
manufacturing something that

00:19:40.800 --> 00:19:42.720 align:middle line:90%
would be generally acceptable."

00:19:42.720 --> 00:19:43.980 align:middle line:90%
End quote.

00:19:43.980 --> 00:19:45.900 align:middle line:84%
So here, we're talking
about a false flag.

00:19:45.900 --> 00:19:48.000 align:middle line:84%
It could be a bombing,
some sort of attack

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:51.570 align:middle line:84%
carried out by the United States
against the United States,

00:19:51.570 --> 00:19:53.550 align:middle line:90%
blamed on the Cubans.

00:19:53.550 --> 00:19:56.550 align:middle line:84%
Meanwhile, the CIA had been
organizing a secret operation

00:19:56.550 --> 00:19:59.850 align:middle line:84%
in Guatemala with the help
of some Cuban exiles known

00:19:59.850 --> 00:20:02.310 align:middle line:90%
as Brigade 2506.

00:20:02.310 --> 00:20:03.960 align:middle line:84%
The CIA was still
under the direction

00:20:03.960 --> 00:20:07.170 align:middle line:84%
of Allen Dulles, who had pulled
off the Iranian and Guatemalan

00:20:07.170 --> 00:20:09.570 align:middle line:90%
operations so successfully.

00:20:09.570 --> 00:20:11.250 align:middle line:84%
The man who oversaw
what would become

00:20:11.250 --> 00:20:13.110 align:middle line:84%
known as the Bay
of Pigs Invasion

00:20:13.110 --> 00:20:15.510 align:middle line:90%
was the CIA's Richard Bissell.

00:20:15.510 --> 00:20:18.360 align:middle line:10%
Many of the agents Bissell
used for the Cuban operation

00:20:18.360 --> 00:20:21.345 align:middle line:10%
had worked for the
1954 Guatemalan coup.

00:20:21.345 --> 00:20:24.930 align:middle line:84%
Now, the thing to keep in mind
about the Bay of Pigs Invasion

00:20:24.930 --> 00:20:26.850 align:middle line:84%
was that the world
was not supposed

00:20:26.850 --> 00:20:29.190 align:middle line:90%
to know the US was behind it.

00:20:29.190 --> 00:20:30.990 align:middle line:84%
As incredible as
that sounds, that's

00:20:30.990 --> 00:20:32.610 align:middle line:90%
how it was supposed to go down.

00:20:32.610 --> 00:20:34.350 align:middle line:84%
The whole thing was
supposed to appear

00:20:34.350 --> 00:20:38.390 align:middle line:84%
to the world to be a
Cuban operation entirely.

00:20:38.390 --> 00:20:41.270 align:middle line:84%
Kennedy in particular
felt very strongly

00:20:41.270 --> 00:20:45.200 align:middle line:84%
that the US needed deniability
of the whole action.

00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:48.020 align:middle line:84%
After all, we're talking
about a fairly open invasion

00:20:48.020 --> 00:20:51.770 align:middle line:84%
of a sovereign country, even
if it was one they didn't like.

00:20:51.770 --> 00:20:54.770 align:middle line:84%
That meant any airpower had
to seem as though it came

00:20:54.770 --> 00:20:56.600 align:middle line:90%
from the Cubans themselves.

00:20:56.600 --> 00:20:59.570 align:middle line:84%
So a day and a half before
the actual invasion,

00:20:59.570 --> 00:21:04.790 align:middle line:84%
on April 15, 1961, three
groups of B26 bombers

00:21:04.790 --> 00:21:08.900 align:middle line:84%
bombed three Cuban airfields
near Havana and Santiago.

00:21:08.900 --> 00:21:11.920 align:middle line:10%
They were painted to look
like stolen Cuban planes,

00:21:11.920 --> 00:21:14.540 align:middle line:10%
and their goal was to
destroy most or all

00:21:14.540 --> 00:21:17.060 align:middle line:10%
of the armed aircraft
of the Cuban Air Force

00:21:17.060 --> 00:21:19.620 align:middle line:10%
in preparation for
the main invasion.

00:21:19.620 --> 00:21:22.640 align:middle line:84%
However, it turned out
that Castro and his people

00:21:22.640 --> 00:21:25.190 align:middle line:84%
knew about the raid and
had moved his planes out

00:21:25.190 --> 00:21:26.900 align:middle line:90%
of harm's way.

00:21:26.900 --> 00:21:28.820 align:middle line:84%
Kennedy realized things
were not looking good,

00:21:28.820 --> 00:21:30.410 align:middle line:90%
but it was too late to stop.

00:21:30.410 --> 00:21:33.410 align:middle line:84%
On April 17, the
Cuban exile brigade

00:21:33.410 --> 00:21:35.960 align:middle line:84%
began its invasion
at an isolated spot

00:21:35.960 --> 00:21:39.200 align:middle line:84%
on Cuba's southern shore
known as the Bay of Pigs.

00:21:39.200 --> 00:21:42.140 align:middle line:84%
Right away, the
invasion was a disaster.

00:21:42.140 --> 00:21:44.660 align:middle line:84%
Unexpected coral
reefs, paratroopers

00:21:44.660 --> 00:21:47.870 align:middle line:84%
landing in the wrong places,
and even a Cuban radio station

00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:50.780 align:middle line:84%
on the beach
broadcasting every detail

00:21:50.780 --> 00:21:52.610 align:middle line:90%
to listeners across Cuba.

00:21:52.610 --> 00:21:54.990 align:middle line:84%
Castro's troops soon
pinned down the invaders,

00:21:54.990 --> 00:21:56.760 align:middle line:90%
and they quickly surrendered.

00:21:56.760 --> 00:21:58.910 align:middle line:10%
Kennedy, the
brand-new President,

00:21:58.910 --> 00:22:01.680 align:middle line:10%
had egg all over his face.

00:22:01.680 --> 00:22:03.260 align:middle line:84%
But this did not
stop the attempt

00:22:03.260 --> 00:22:07.070 align:middle line:84%
to create false flags and
regime change against Cuba.

00:22:07.070 --> 00:22:09.560 align:middle line:84%
Most famously, there
was Operation Mongoose

00:22:09.560 --> 00:22:13.010 align:middle line:84%
led by US Air Force
General Edward Lansdale.

00:22:13.010 --> 00:22:14.870 align:middle line:84%
This included a
wide-ranging plan

00:22:14.870 --> 00:22:17.450 align:middle line:84%
from spreading
propaganda inside Cuba

00:22:17.450 --> 00:22:20.210 align:middle line:84%
to enlisting resistance
forces to disrupting

00:22:20.210 --> 00:22:22.400 align:middle line:84%
the Cuban government
and economy,

00:22:22.400 --> 00:22:25.250 align:middle line:84%
destroying sugar crops,
railways, bridges,

00:22:25.250 --> 00:22:29.830 align:middle line:84%
oil refinery, and mining
harbors using US special forces.

00:22:29.830 --> 00:22:31.430 align:middle line:90%
Mongoose didn't last long.

00:22:31.430 --> 00:22:34.820 align:middle line:90%
Kennedy pulled the plug in 1962.

00:22:34.820 --> 00:22:38.300 align:middle line:84%
The most shocking false flag
planned during this period

00:22:38.300 --> 00:22:40.250 align:middle line:84%
thankfully was
never implemented.

00:22:40.250 --> 00:22:42.770 align:middle line:90%
This was Operation Northwoods.

00:22:42.770 --> 00:22:46.100 align:middle line:84%
Remember when Eisenhower had
been pining for a manufactured

00:22:46.100 --> 00:22:47.900 align:middle line:90%
excuse to invade Cuba?

00:22:47.900 --> 00:22:50.240 align:middle line:84%
Well, the idea
stayed in the head

00:22:50.240 --> 00:22:52.850 align:middle line:84%
of the chairman of the Joint
Chiefs of Staff, General Lyman

00:22:52.850 --> 00:22:54.260 align:middle line:90%
Lemnitzer.

00:22:54.260 --> 00:22:57.050 align:middle line:84%
Lemnitzer decided
that the US would

00:22:57.050 --> 00:23:00.230 align:middle line:84%
have to trick the American
public and the world

00:23:00.230 --> 00:23:03.380 align:middle line:84%
into hating Cuba so much
that they would sign

00:23:03.380 --> 00:23:05.840 align:middle line:90%
on to a war against Castro.

00:23:05.840 --> 00:23:08.690 align:middle line:84%
Operation Northwoods was
actually a series of ideas,

00:23:08.690 --> 00:23:11.390 align:middle line:84%
none of which came to
fruition, but all of which

00:23:11.390 --> 00:23:15.020 align:middle line:84%
required false flags to
justify a war with Cuba.

00:23:15.020 --> 00:23:16.670 align:middle line:84%
Probably the most
outrageous of them

00:23:16.670 --> 00:23:19.340 align:middle line:84%
considered the
launch of John Glenn,

00:23:19.340 --> 00:23:21.920 align:middle line:84%
who was the first American
to orbit the Earth.

00:23:21.920 --> 00:23:25.250 align:middle line:84%
On February 20, 1962,
Glenn was to lift off

00:23:25.250 --> 00:23:28.910 align:middle line:84%
from Cape Canaveral, Florida
on his historic journey.

00:23:28.910 --> 00:23:31.250 align:middle line:10%
Lemnitzer and his
Chiefs actually

00:23:31.250 --> 00:23:35.690 align:middle line:10%
proposed to Lansdale that if the
rocket were to explode and kill

00:23:35.690 --> 00:23:39.650 align:middle line:10%
Glenn, they would provide,
quote, "irrevocable proof

00:23:39.650 --> 00:23:42.320 align:middle line:10%
that the communists
and Cubans did it."

00:23:42.320 --> 00:23:44.660 align:middle line:10%
They would do this--
and this is a quote--

00:23:44.660 --> 00:23:47.870 align:middle line:10%
"by manufacturing various
pieces of evidence

00:23:47.870 --> 00:23:50.960 align:middle line:10%
which would prove electronic
interference on the part

00:23:50.960 --> 00:23:53.150 align:middle line:10%
of the Cubans," end quote.

00:23:53.150 --> 00:23:56.390 align:middle line:84%
So just consider--
just as NASA prepared

00:23:56.390 --> 00:23:59.150 align:middle line:84%
to send the first
American into space,

00:23:59.150 --> 00:24:01.250 align:middle line:84%
the Joint Chiefs of
Staff were preparing

00:24:01.250 --> 00:24:05.410 align:middle line:84%
to use John Glenn's death
as a pretext to begin a war.

00:24:05.410 --> 00:24:07.650 align:middle line:84%
Well, fortunately,
that did not happen.

00:24:07.650 --> 00:24:10.850 align:middle line:84%
So Lemnitzer and the Chiefs
developed other ideas.

00:24:10.850 --> 00:24:14.660 align:middle line:84%
One was a series of incidents to
take place at the US Navy base

00:24:14.660 --> 00:24:17.330 align:middle line:84%
at Guantanamo Bay,
Cuba, such as dressing

00:24:17.330 --> 00:24:20.210 align:middle line:84%
friendly Cubans in
Cuban military uniforms

00:24:20.210 --> 00:24:23.840 align:middle line:84%
and then have them start riots
near the main gate of the base.

00:24:23.840 --> 00:24:27.080 align:middle line:84%
Others would pretend to be
saboteurs inside the base.

00:24:27.080 --> 00:24:29.210 align:middle line:84%
Ammunition would be
blown up, fires started,

00:24:29.210 --> 00:24:32.540 align:middle line:84%
aircraft sabotaged, mortars
fired at the base with damage

00:24:32.540 --> 00:24:33.965 align:middle line:90%
to installations.

00:24:33.965 --> 00:24:37.160 align:middle line:84%
And if this reminds you a bit
of the German invasion of Poland

00:24:37.160 --> 00:24:40.610 align:middle line:90%
from 1935, then you're learning.

00:24:40.610 --> 00:24:42.230 align:middle line:84%
Another of Lemnitzer's
ideas called

00:24:42.230 --> 00:24:45.560 align:middle line:84%
for blowing up a US
ship in Guantanamo Bay

00:24:45.560 --> 00:24:46.820 align:middle line:90%
and blaming Cuba.

00:24:46.820 --> 00:24:51.500 align:middle line:84%
That one sounds, of course,
like the USS Maine of 1898.

00:24:51.500 --> 00:24:54.500 align:middle line:84%
Other ideas included developing
a Cuban terror campaign

00:24:54.500 --> 00:24:58.910 align:middle line:84%
in Miami or in Washington,
sinking a boatload of Cubans

00:24:58.910 --> 00:25:02.000 align:middle line:84%
en route to Florida,
whether real or simulated,

00:25:02.000 --> 00:25:04.940 align:middle line:84%
kill or wound Cuban refugees
in the United States,

00:25:04.940 --> 00:25:07.505 align:middle line:84%
and of course giving
them wide publicity.

00:25:07.505 --> 00:25:11.050 align:middle line:84%
Now, all of these were to
be blamed on Castro's Cuba.

00:25:11.050 --> 00:25:14.480 align:middle line:84%
Lemnitzer also proposed
bombings and hijackings

00:25:14.480 --> 00:25:16.310 align:middle line:84%
that would implicate
the Cuban government.

00:25:16.310 --> 00:25:18.620 align:middle line:84%
Some of the most outrageous
of these involved making it

00:25:18.620 --> 00:25:21.530 align:middle line:84%
seem that a Cuban aircraft
had attacked and shot

00:25:21.530 --> 00:25:23.910 align:middle line:90%
down a chartered civil airliner.

00:25:23.910 --> 00:25:26.840 align:middle line:84%
Another was to make it appear
that the Cubans had shot down

00:25:26.840 --> 00:25:29.690 align:middle line:84%
an American fighter jet
over international waters

00:25:29.690 --> 00:25:32.100 align:middle line:90%
in an unprovoked attack.

00:25:32.100 --> 00:25:35.840 align:middle line:84%
All of this was
proposed in March 1962.

00:25:35.840 --> 00:25:38.980 align:middle line:84%
I think Kennedy was
astounded by all of this.

00:25:38.980 --> 00:25:42.850 align:middle line:10%
He simply told Lemnitzer there
was virtually no possibility

00:25:42.850 --> 00:25:46.510 align:middle line:10%
that the US would ever use
overt military force in Cuba.

00:25:46.510 --> 00:25:48.970 align:middle line:84%
The whole plan was shelved
and remained secret

00:25:48.970 --> 00:25:50.855 align:middle line:90%
for the next 40 years.

00:25:50.855 --> 00:25:52.480 align:middle line:84%
All notes were thought
to be destroyed,

00:25:52.480 --> 00:25:56.260 align:middle line:84%
but apparently, this body
wasn't fully buried after all.

00:25:56.260 --> 00:25:58.330 align:middle line:84%
Operation Northwoods
was finally revealed

00:25:58.330 --> 00:26:02.560 align:middle line:84%
to the public in a 2003 book by
researcher and historian James

00:26:02.560 --> 00:26:03.550 align:middle line:90%
Bamford.

00:26:03.550 --> 00:26:05.110 align:middle line:84%
President Kennedy
was assassinated

00:26:05.110 --> 00:26:08.830 align:middle line:84%
in November 1963, an event that
rightfully should be considered

00:26:08.830 --> 00:26:12.670 align:middle line:84%
a false flag much like Stalin's
assassination of Sergey Kirov

00:26:12.670 --> 00:26:13.990 align:middle line:90%
three decades earlier.

00:26:13.990 --> 00:26:16.690 align:middle line:84%
In any case, less than
a year after that,

00:26:16.690 --> 00:26:19.570 align:middle line:84%
one of the most critical false
flags of the 20th century

00:26:19.570 --> 00:26:22.720 align:middle line:84%
took place at a place
called the Gulf of Tonkin

00:26:22.720 --> 00:26:25.480 align:middle line:90%
on August 2, 1964.

00:26:25.480 --> 00:26:28.270 align:middle line:84%
Lyndon Johnson was now
America's President.

00:26:28.270 --> 00:26:31.690 align:middle line:84%
Hostilities had been going on in
Vietnam since the Second World

00:26:31.690 --> 00:26:35.620 align:middle line:84%
War, and all through the 1950s
and '60s, the US had been

00:26:35.620 --> 00:26:38.200 align:middle line:84%
managing things from
behind the curtain--

00:26:38.200 --> 00:26:40.480 align:middle line:84%
preventing Vietnam
from becoming unified,

00:26:40.480 --> 00:26:43.480 align:middle line:84%
arming and controlling the
government in South Vietnam,

00:26:43.480 --> 00:26:47.020 align:middle line:84%
a government that was so
unpopular that Buddhist monks

00:26:47.020 --> 00:26:50.620 align:middle line:84%
began lighting themselves
on fire in protest.

00:26:50.620 --> 00:26:53.180 align:middle line:84%
But Johnson didn't want
to tone things down.

00:26:53.180 --> 00:26:55.330 align:middle line:84%
He wanted to ratchet
them up and escalate

00:26:55.330 --> 00:26:57.324 align:middle line:90%
an already unpopular war.

00:26:57.324 --> 00:26:58.990 align:middle line:84%
It could help make
money for his friends

00:26:58.990 --> 00:27:00.800 align:middle line:90%
who owned defense corporations.

00:27:00.800 --> 00:27:03.730 align:middle line:84%
He could also get the
Pentagon and CIA off his back

00:27:03.730 --> 00:27:07.510 align:middle line:84%
and quit trying to invade Cuba,
which was no longer feasible.

00:27:07.510 --> 00:27:10.660 align:middle line:84%
But he needed a provocation to
convince the American people

00:27:10.660 --> 00:27:12.940 align:middle line:84%
that the war had
to be escalated.

00:27:12.940 --> 00:27:16.090 align:middle line:84%
And then on August
2, a sea battle

00:27:16.090 --> 00:27:19.180 align:middle line:84%
occurred between the United
States and North Vietnam

00:27:19.180 --> 00:27:20.890 align:middle line:90%
in Vietnamese waters.

00:27:20.890 --> 00:27:23.050 align:middle line:90%
This was the Gulf of Tonkin.

00:27:23.050 --> 00:27:25.950 align:middle line:84%
Both sides experienced
damage to their vessels,

00:27:25.950 --> 00:27:28.060 align:middle line:84%
and the North
Vietnamese lost four men

00:27:28.060 --> 00:27:30.340 align:middle line:90%
and suffered six casualties.

00:27:30.340 --> 00:27:32.560 align:middle line:84%
Two days later, the
National Security Agency

00:27:32.560 --> 00:27:35.890 align:middle line:84%
claimed that a similar
battle had taken place.

00:27:35.890 --> 00:27:38.560 align:middle line:84%
What actually happened
is that the USS Maddox

00:27:38.560 --> 00:27:40.930 align:middle line:84%
was engaged in
electronic espionage

00:27:40.930 --> 00:27:44.140 align:middle line:84%
against North Vietnam,
coordinating attacks

00:27:44.140 --> 00:27:47.230 align:middle line:84%
by South Vietnam and
the Laotian Air Force

00:27:47.230 --> 00:27:49.550 align:middle line:84%
against North
Vietnamese targets.

00:27:49.550 --> 00:27:52.480 align:middle line:84%
They were doing this in North
Vietnamese waters, which

00:27:52.480 --> 00:27:54.190 align:middle line:90%
is an act of war.

00:27:54.190 --> 00:27:56.170 align:middle line:84%
On August 2, the
North Vietnamese,

00:27:56.170 --> 00:27:59.020 align:middle line:84%
knowing this was going
on, attacked the Maddox,

00:27:59.020 --> 00:28:01.630 align:middle line:84%
rather ineffectively,
as you might imagine.

00:28:01.630 --> 00:28:04.590 align:middle line:84%
There was never any
evidence of a second attack.

00:28:04.590 --> 00:28:07.870 align:middle line:84%
But on August 5,
newspapers across America

00:28:07.870 --> 00:28:10.390 align:middle line:84%
reported this as a
series of attacks

00:28:10.390 --> 00:28:11.950 align:middle line:90%
against American vessels.

00:28:11.950 --> 00:28:14.050 align:middle line:84%
People were told that
North Vietnamese torpedo

00:28:14.050 --> 00:28:17.860 align:middle line:84%
boats launched an unprovoked
attack while the Maddox was

00:28:17.860 --> 00:28:20.080 align:middle line:90%
on a routine patrol.

00:28:20.080 --> 00:28:22.720 align:middle line:84%
>> REPORTER: Swift and sure
has been US retaliation

00:28:22.720 --> 00:28:25.360 align:middle line:84%
for communist PT boat
attacks on the high seas.

00:28:25.360 --> 00:28:27.970 align:middle line:84%
This is the Maddox, one
of the two destroyers

00:28:27.970 --> 00:28:30.700 align:middle line:84%
that were attacked while
patrolling international waters

00:28:30.700 --> 00:28:33.370 align:middle line:84%
in the Gulf of Tonkin
near North Vietnam.

00:28:33.370 --> 00:28:35.615 align:middle line:84%
War planes from two
carriers, the Ticonderoga

00:28:35.615 --> 00:28:39.210 align:middle line:84%
and the Constellation, avenged
the unwarranted red assault

00:28:39.210 --> 00:28:42.884 align:middle line:84%
with 64 sorties to
North Vietnam PT basins.

00:28:42.884 --> 00:28:45.050 align:middle line:84%
>> RICHARD: President Johnson
added the attacks were

00:28:45.050 --> 00:28:48.410 align:middle line:84%
on the high seas, which
meant international waters,

00:28:48.410 --> 00:28:50.490 align:middle line:90%
but this was not true.

00:28:50.490 --> 00:28:53.910 align:middle line:84%
Johnson also knew the second
attack never happened.

00:28:53.910 --> 00:28:56.610 align:middle line:84%
Captain John J. Herrick,
the task force commander

00:28:56.610 --> 00:28:59.040 align:middle line:84%
in the Gulf, had
cabled Washington

00:28:59.040 --> 00:29:02.370 align:middle line:84%
that the second report was the
result of an overeager sonar

00:29:02.370 --> 00:29:06.690 align:middle line:84%
man who had picked up the sounds
of his own ship and panicked.

00:29:06.690 --> 00:29:09.420 align:middle line:84%
The US media relied
almost exclusively

00:29:09.420 --> 00:29:12.240 align:middle line:84%
on US government officials
for its information

00:29:12.240 --> 00:29:15.030 align:middle line:84%
and almost completely
avoided any questioning

00:29:15.030 --> 00:29:16.230 align:middle line:90%
of what actually happened.

00:29:16.230 --> 00:29:19.140 align:middle line:10%
>> WAYNE MORSE: At the time,
I referred to it as another

00:29:19.140 --> 00:29:21.810 align:middle line:10%
sinking of the Maine.

00:29:21.810 --> 00:29:23.400 align:middle line:10%
>> INTERVIEWER: Suggesting?

00:29:23.400 --> 00:29:26.880 align:middle line:10%
>> MORSE: Well, you know what
the best historical advice is

00:29:26.880 --> 00:29:29.710 align:middle line:10%
in regard to the
sinking of the Maine.

00:29:29.710 --> 00:29:32.220 align:middle line:10%
It was a deliberate act on
the part of the United States

00:29:32.220 --> 00:29:35.190 align:middle line:10%
to have an excuse to go
to war against Spain.

00:29:35.190 --> 00:29:38.010 align:middle line:10%
The Gulf of Tonkin was a
deliberate aggressive act

00:29:38.010 --> 00:29:39.900 align:middle line:10%
on the part of the
Johnson administration

00:29:39.900 --> 00:29:43.590 align:middle line:10%
to justify making war
against North Vietnam.

00:29:43.590 --> 00:29:46.230 align:middle line:84%
>> RICHARD: The rest followed
sadly and predictably.

00:29:46.230 --> 00:29:49.410 align:middle line:84%
The US Congress gave permission
for massive air strikes

00:29:49.410 --> 00:29:52.440 align:middle line:84%
on North Vietnam and a
dramatically ramped-up US

00:29:52.440 --> 00:29:55.020 align:middle line:84%
involvement there up to more
than half a million troops

00:29:55.020 --> 00:29:56.160 align:middle line:90%
at a time.

00:29:56.160 --> 00:29:58.082 align:middle line:10%
>> LYNDON JOHNSON: When
the going got hard,

00:29:58.082 --> 00:30:01.680 align:middle line:10%
when the road got
longer and dustier,

00:30:01.680 --> 00:30:05.960 align:middle line:10%
when the casualties
started coming in, why,

00:30:05.960 --> 00:30:10.050 align:middle line:10%
there's certain folks started
looking for the seller.

00:30:10.050 --> 00:30:13.195 align:middle line:10%
I know they-- or a
good many of them have,

00:30:13.195 --> 00:30:18.180 align:middle line:10%
and I don't question
their right to do so.

00:30:18.180 --> 00:30:21.030 align:middle line:10%


00:30:21.030 --> 00:30:26.330 align:middle line:10%
I don't even criticize them
for taking that position,

00:30:26.330 --> 00:30:28.801 align:middle line:10%
if that's what their
conscience dictates.

00:30:28.801 --> 00:30:31.300 align:middle line:10%
I just wish their conscience
had been operating when they're

00:30:31.300 --> 00:30:32.910 align:middle line:10%
making all these
